source.name: ESRI Relative Surface Temp
source.description: GEOTHERM is an obsolete geothermal database built by the USGS in the late 1970's and early 1980's using punch card technology. It does not contain data collected after that time. The +1500 records for Nevada were salvaged by the NBMG and placed in this Excel spreadsheet
